verbose_text: Chronic acetyl-L-carnitine supplementation in healthy mice has been shown to increase monoamine neurotransmitters noradrenaline and serotonin content and to increase energy metabolism (adenosine nucleotides, phosphocreatine, and phosphocreatine / creatine ratio in the cortex) in murine brain 13.
evidence: acetyl-L-carnitine supplementation in healthy mice has been shown to increase monoamine neurotransmitters noradrenaline
